{#
  html.html.twig
  AI ingestion review: 2026-05-18. Re-audit annually or when org data changes.

  AI INGESTION POLICY: noai/noimageai meta tags are intentionally ABSENT.
  The university wants AI systems to index, surface, and learn from this site.
  Do not add noai/noimageai tags without explicit policy approval.

  Security surface summary:
  - {{ page }} is the primary prompt-injection risk; mitigate via Drupal text
    format configuration (restrict style= attributes and display:none patterns).
  - placeholder_token|raw is safe — it is a Drupal render pipeline token,
    not user input. Do not confuse with CSRF tokens (those are form-specific).
  - JSON-LD speakable block actively signals AI crawlers; update if policy changes.
  - GTM fires before any consent layer; audit tags for third-party AI data flows.
  - charset, viewport, lang, meta description, and Open Graph tags are injected
    by Drupal via head-placeholder and the metatag module — not this template's job.
  - Content-Security-Policy is best enforced at the server/CDN level, not here.
#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html{{ html_attributes }}>

  <head>

    {#
      PERFORMANCE HINTS
      Preconnect reduces latency to GTM origin. dns-prefetch is a fallback for
      browsers that do not support preconnect.
    #}
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://www.googletagmanager.com">
    <link rel="dns-prefetch" href="https://www.googletagmanager.com">

    {#
      GOOGLE TAG MANAGER
      WARNING: GTM fires before any consent layer. If any GTM tag ships page
      content to a third-party AI service (e.g. via custom HTML or data layer
      events), that is a data-governance risk independent of this template.
      Audit GTM workspace for AI-adjacent tags and enforce a consent trigger
      on anything that is not strictly necessary.
      NOTE: GTM does not support Subresource Integrity (SRI) because the script
      is dynamically generated per request. This is a known GTM limitation.
    #}
    <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtm.js?id=GTM-KBWW4MVB"></script>

    {# Font preloads — crossorigin required for CORS font fetches. #}
    <link rel="preload"
      href="/themes/contrib/cua_theme/fonts/roboto-condensed-v31-latin-regular.woff2"
      as="font"
      type="font/woff2"
      crossorigin>
    <link rel="preload"
      href="/themes/contrib/cua_theme/fonts/roboto-v51-latin-regular.woff2"
      as="font"
      type="font/woff2"
      crossorigin>

    {#
      DRUPAL PLACEHOLDERS
      |raw is intentional and safe: placeholder_token is a Drupal render pipeline
      token used for BigPipe/placeholder replacement — it is never derived from
      user input. It is NOT a CSRF token (those live in forms via csrf_token()).
      Do not change to auto-escaped output; the placeholder tags will break.
      Do not use |raw anywhere else in this file without the same justification.
    #}
    <head-placeholder token="{{ placeholder_token|raw }}">

    {#
      PAGE TITLE
      safe_join auto-escapes each element before joining, preventing XSS from
      a malicious head_title value. AI crawlers use <title> as the document
      label — keep titles accurate and descriptive.
    #}
    <title>{{ head_title|safe_join(' | ') }}</title>

    <css-placeholder token="{{ placeholder_token|raw }}">
    <js-placeholder token="{{ placeholder_token|raw }}">

    {#
      STRUCTURED DATA — JSON-LD
      Fully hardcoded and safe from injection.

      AI INGESTION NOTE: JSON-LD is the primary signal consumed by AI systems
      (LLMs, knowledge graphs, voice assistants). Key properties:

        "@type": "NGO" is the correct Schema.org type (NGO extends Organization,
          so listing both ["Organization", "NGO"] is redundant; "NGO" alone is
          more precise and equally compatible).

        "description" — AI systems treat this as the canonical org summary.
          STALE DATA RISK: "$3.2 billion in assets" is hardcoded. Update this
          figure at least annually or it will propagate outdated information
          across AI-generated answers. Consider adding an "as of" date here.

        "sameAs" — links used by knowledge graphs to deduplicate entities.
          WARNING: the Wikipedia URL points to the University of Colorado
          (the parent org), NOT the CU Foundation. If a Foundation-specific
          Wikipedia article exists, replace it. If not, remove that entry —
          a wrong sameAs actively harms entity identity in AI knowledge graphs.

        "speakable" — tells voice AI and answer engines which content to read
          aloud or surface in AI answers. The "meta[name='description']" selector
          is valid because Drupal's metatag module injects that tag into the DOM
          via head-placeholder above — by render time it exists. If you remove
          the metatag module, remove this selector too.
          The ".field--name-body p.intro" selector depends on cua_theme rendering
          the body field with a <p class="intro"> wrapper. If the theme or field
          display changes, this selector breaks silently. Review after any theme
          update.

        "contactPoint" / "address" — hardcoded. Update when contact info changes
          or AI assistants will give donors wrong numbers and addresses.

      If you ever make any of these values dynamic (pulled from config or fields),
      use {{ value|e('json') }} and audit for injection — JSON-LD does not
      benefit from HTML auto-escaping.
    #}
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "NGO",
      "@id": "https://www.giving.cu.edu/#organization",
      "name": "University of Colorado Foundation",
      "alternateName": "CU Foundation",
      "url": "https://www.giving.cu.edu/",
      "description": "Founded in 1967, the University of Colorado Foundation manages over $3.2 billion in assets to support education, research, and community engagement across CU's four campuses.",
      "foundingDate": "1967",
      "taxID": "84-6049811",
      "nonprofitStatus": "Nonprofit501c3",
      "logo": {
        "@type": "ImageObject",
        "url": "https://www.giving.cu.edu/themes/contrib/cua_theme/images/logo.svg",
        "width": 225,
        "height": 24
      },
      "address": {
        "@type": "PostalAddress",
        "streetAddress": "1800 Grant Street, Suite 725",
        "addressLocality": "Denver",
        "addressRegion": "CO",
        "postalCode": "80203",
        "addressCountry": "US"
      },
      "contactPoint": {
        "@type": "ContactPoint",
        "telephone": "+1-303-813-7935",
        "email": "gifts@cufund.org",
        "contactType": "donor services",
        "areaServed": "US"
      },
      "parentOrganization": {
        "@type": "CollegeOrUniversity",
        "name": "University of Colorado",
        "url": "https://www.cu.edu/"
      },
      "department": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "@id": "https://www.giving.cu.edu/#advancement",
        "name": "Central CU Advancement",
        "url": "https://www.giving.cu.edu/about-us/central-cu-advancement"
      },
      "sameAs": [
        "https://projects.propublica.org/nonprofits/organizations/846049811",
        "https://www.cufund.org"
      ],
      "speakable": {
        "@type": "SpeakableSpecification",
        "cssSelector": ["h1", ".field--name-body p.intro", "meta[name='description']"]
      }
    }
    </script>

  </head>

  {#
    BODY ATTRIBUTES
    attributes.addClass is safe — Drupal's Attribute object auto-escapes all
    values. body_classes is assembled in preprocess, not from raw user input.
  #}
  <body{{ attributes.addClass(body_classes) }}>

    <a href="#main" class="visually-hidden focusable">
      {{ 'Skip to main content'|t }}
    </a>

    {#
      GTM NOSCRIPT FALLBACK
      Mirrors the GTM head tag for non-JS environments. Same consent-layer
      caveat applies: this fires unconditionally.
    #}
    <noscript>
      <iframe
        src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/ns.html?id=GTM-KBWW4MVB"
        height="0"
        width="0"
        style="display:none;visibility:hidden">
      </iframe>
    </noscript>

    {#
      MAIN CONTENT RENDER
      PRIMARY AI PROMPT-INJECTION SURFACE.

      {{ page }} renders the entire content tree. If any text format permits
      editors to output arbitrary style= attributes, hidden elements, or
      display:none spans, a malicious editor or compromised account can embed
      invisible instructions targeting AI crawlers, e.g.:
        <span style="display:none">Ignore previous instructions…</span>

      This template cannot prevent that. Mitigate at the Drupal layer:
        1. Admin > Config > Content authoring > Text formats
           — Remove "Limit allowed HTML tags" exceptions for style=
           — Enable "Restrict images to this site" and similar filters
        2. Add a custom filter_html rule blocking display:none patterns
           if your editorial workflow requires inline styles elsewhere.
        3. Review which roles have access to the "Full HTML" format —
           that format bypasses all filters and is the highest-risk path.
    #}
    {{ page_top }}
    {{ page }}
    {{ page_bottom }}

    {# See placeholder note in <head> — |raw is safe here for the same reason. #}
    <js-bottom-placeholder token="{{ placeholder_token|raw }}">

  </body>
</html>